{
  "stem": "27748.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, unfortunately, he died before I could communicate that to him, that my sense of appreciation for him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Chapel Hill then was a very different, much more professionally oriented research university.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And there-- I was there from 1952, first for one year.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then I-- at that time, I decided that I would go in the army for two years to get the GI bill.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I was in the army for two years, and then came back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So, financially, it was a little easier, but I also had an assistantship for the rest of the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in the Infantry School at Fort Benning, most of the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fort Benning is sort of the center of the infantry system in the army, for training infantry officers, and this, and so on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Well, first of all, a regimentation was not strange to me, except to my recollection, I never said sir in the two years to anybody.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember ever saying sir.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- so something in me remained independent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But, anyway, I was an enlisted man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A finally made it up to corporal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was a good boy, in a sense.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my main job was being a clerk typist in an office.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so one of the things that I recall from that experience was that we kept records of people who went for refresher courses in the Infantry School.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I was-- the German word is-- there's a German word called [GERMAN], being pleased about the misfortune of others.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, I was very pleased when high officers came to the office to look at their grades and were very scared about making a poor grade.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
